author: China Insights
description:
This fall, China did something unprecedented—it didn’t buy a single U.S. soybean. Trump quickly declared that he will face off with Xi Jinping at APEC in four weeks. This “soybean war” is no longer just about food; it’s a life-or-death gamble between Trump’s voter base and Xi’s regime. At the same time, Beijing’s Fourth Plenum is approaching, with infighting, health rumors, and cross-Strait undercurrents all erupting.

Food war, power struggle, or Taiwan Strait conflict—which will ignite first?Welcome to China Insights — your window into the real China, beyond the veil.
With sharp analysis and a touch of dry humor, we dive into the social unrest, economic crises, censorship, faith suppression, and human rights challenges shaping China today.
We spotlight authentic Chinese culture, deliver timely and uncensored news, break down key economic trends, and explore shifting social dynamics — all while exposing the Chinese Communist Party’s complex roles both at home and on the global stage.
title: Soy Shock: Trump–Xi Showdown

author: China Insights
description:
North Korea’s foreign minister has visited China twice in one month, sparking talk that Xi Jinping may be preparing a “last-resort escape route” — with Pyongyang as the destination? Meanwhile, a detail from a Xinjiang celebration showing Wang Huning with his hands clasped behind his back has ignited heated debate. Rumors of flight plus power signals: on the eve of the Fourth Plenum, the political winds have suddenly shifted!
